to the editor a june 14 letter suggests that elite universities make a deal with the admirals and generals asking them to discontinue the 'do n't ask do n't tell policy about homosexuality in the military however the pentagon does not have the power to make such a deal the rules about homosexuality are not pentagon policy they are federal law passed by a democratic house and senate in 1993 and signed by a democratic president president bill clinton expended a lot of political capital in the struggle over this law and there is little enthusiasm in washington for resuming the fight harvard 's president lawrence h summers who served in president clinton 's cabinet understands this and has pushed for an atmosphere supportive of the rotc cadets at harvard within the framework of the law and the traditions of openness at harvard michael m segal boston june 14 2002 the writer is a steering committee member advocates for harvard rotc

